WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:58.160
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:15.080
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.390 --> 00:01:45.920
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:50.470 --> 00:01:54.660
Gum-Gum..

24
00:01:51.100 --> 00:01:52.880
K-King Wapol! It's Straw Hat!

25
00:01:53.270 --> 00:01:53.760
Ah!

26
00:01:55.470 --> 00:01:57.310
...Pistol!

27
00:02:01.650 --> 00:02:03.480
– King Wapol!
– King Wapol!

28
00:02:15.030 --> 00:02:17.200
That was close...

29
00:02:21.450 --> 00:02:25.380
Unbreakable

30
00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:25.380
You bastards... How dare you!

31
00:02:27.640 --> 00:02:29.210
Again and again...

32
00:02:29.210 --> 00:02:31.840
How many times are you
gonna stand in our way?!

33
00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:35.010
Hm? Why are they here?

34
00:02:38.970 --> 00:02:43.090
Last time I had to run away
since my friend was injured.

35
00:02:43.090 --> 00:02:48.080
But this time...
there's no need to hold back!

36
00:02:49.900 --> 00:02:51.530
You worthless scoundrel!

37
00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:56.840
The nerve you have, assaulting
Wapol of the Kingdom of Drum!

38
00:02:56.840 --> 00:02:58.470
He's a king, you know! A king!

39
00:02:58.470 --> 00:03:01.610
His Majesty is the supreme
ruler of this island.

40
00:03:01.610 --> 00:03:03.910
This treatment is deplorable!

41
00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:07.040
Who cares?! You guys piss me off!

42
00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:10.080
Hey, kid. You know them?

43
00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:12.850
Yeah, I do! He's that
annoying big-mouth pirate!

44
00:03:12.850 --> 00:03:13.820
Big-mouth...?

45
00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:15.430
He keeps getting in my way!

46
00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:17.320
He munched on my ship,
attacked my crew...

47
00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:19.160
I'm gonna stop him right here!

48
00:03:19.160 --> 00:03:22.360
More importantly,
aren't you cold in that getup?

49
00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:22.890
Huh?

50
00:03:22.890 --> 00:03:24.560
See?

51
00:03:25.060 --> 00:03:28.350
Wait, did they say he's the king?
Isn't he a pirate?!

52
00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:29.520
That's your problem?!

53
00:03:29.900 --> 00:03:33.840
Ha! What an idiot!
He finally realized his impertinence.

54
00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:36.510
Our liege, Wapol, is the king of Drum.

55
00:03:36.510 --> 00:03:38.450
When you saw him earlier as a pirate,

56
00:03:38.450 --> 00:03:41.080
that was nothing more
than a temporary arrangement.

57
00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:43.450
Now he's done being a pirate,

58
00:03:43.450 --> 00:03:46.500
and has returned to rule
over this great country!

59
00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:48.220
Wow, it's cold up here!

60
00:03:48.220 --> 00:03:49.720
That's what I've been saying!

61
00:03:49.720 --> 00:03:51.420
It's 50 below, you know!

62
00:03:51.420 --> 00:03:53.170
They're making light of us!

63
00:03:54.530 --> 00:03:55.670
King Wapol!

64
00:03:55.930 --> 00:04:00.170
Now I'm really mad... Straw Hat!

65
00:04:00.170 --> 00:04:02.140
I'll bite you to pieces!

66
00:04:02.460 --> 00:04:04.390
Um, you'll have to wait a bit for that.

67
00:04:04.390 --> 00:04:06.520
Luffy went to get some clothes.

68
00:04:06.520 --> 00:04:07.600
He's gone?!

69
00:04:08.110 --> 00:04:09.740
Let me ask you a question.

70
00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:13.250
Earlier... his arm stretched...

71
00:04:13.250 --> 00:04:16.180
Yep, he's stretchy.
He's a rubber man, after all.

72
00:04:16.180 --> 00:04:18.320
Wh... What's that?

73
00:04:19.170 --> 00:04:20.110
It's a monster!

74
00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:24.870
So, long story short,

75
00:04:24.870 --> 00:04:27.830
that rebel of a hag and some 
Straw Hat pirates are in my castle.

76
00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:29.580
Once we eliminate them all,

77
00:04:29.580 --> 00:04:34.570
there won't be anyone else
audacious enough to defy me.

78
00:04:34.570 --> 00:04:36.220
Precisely.

79
00:04:36.700 --> 00:04:40.470
This will go down as the day
the Kingdom of Drum was restored!

80
00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:42.740
And I'll start with you, Dr. Kureha!

81
00:04:42.740 --> 00:04:46.180
You've got some nerve moving
into my castle during my absence...

82
00:04:46.180 --> 00:04:48.140
and even flying a strange flag!

83
00:04:48.650 --> 00:04:52.150
I made this castle Hiriluk's grave.

84
00:04:54.850 --> 00:04:59.090
I really didn't give a damn
about this run-down castle,

85
00:04:59.090 --> 00:05:03.410
but this reindeer insisted
on flying Hiriluk's flag up there.

86
00:05:05.130 --> 00:05:09.870
That's why I raised this skull
and crossbones against all diseases!

87
00:05:10.740 --> 00:05:11.920
A skull...

88
00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:16.590
This here... is a symbol of conviction
that defies the impossible!

89
00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:21.090
I'll save this country as a doctor!

90
00:05:21.610 --> 00:05:25.220
By raising this flag,
I'll fight just like pirates do!

91
00:05:25.820 --> 00:05:31.230
In raising this flag...
Doctor fought to save this country!

92
00:05:36.110 --> 00:05:40.280
How dare you sully my sacred castle
with that cretin's flag!

93
00:05:41.010 --> 00:05:43.240
Burn down that flag at once!

94
00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:50.500
You won't set foot inside this castle...

95
00:05:51.520 --> 00:05:51.870
Huh?!

96
00:05:53.550 --> 00:05:54.660
I won't let you!

97
00:05:55.690 --> 00:05:57.620
King Wapol... it's...

98
00:05:57.620 --> 00:05:59.210
That's right! From back then...!

99
00:06:00.630 --> 00:06:03.690
It's that monster... 
who followed that stupid doctor!

100
00:06:05.970 --> 00:06:08.850
That flag... is Doctor's conviction!

101
00:06:09.570 --> 00:06:11.810
So I won't let you take it down!

102
00:06:12.770 --> 00:06:14.150
I won't let you!

103
00:06:15.910 --> 00:06:18.540
Show them no mercy!
We're going into the castle!

104
00:06:18.540 --> 00:06:21.610
Take down every single one of 'em!

105
00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:24.320
Are you gonna fight, too, old lady?

106
00:06:24.320 --> 00:06:25.320
Old lady?

107
00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:26.280
Ugh!

108
00:06:26.580 --> 00:06:29.410
If they give you trouble,
then I'll lend a hand.

109
00:06:29.410 --> 00:06:30.240
Appreciate it...

110
00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:32.360
Your Majesty! Leave it to us!

111
00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:34.460
These pests are nothing!

112
00:06:34.870 --> 00:06:35.920
Doctorine!

113
00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:41.270
Hey, hey, hey, afro man.

114
00:06:41.270 --> 00:06:45.640
What kind of "soul brother"
throws his afro at a lady?

115
00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:49.060
Hey, that's more like it.

116
00:06:51.840 --> 00:06:52.730
You fell for it...

117
00:06:53.150 --> 00:06:53.560
Huh?

118
00:06:55.560 --> 00:06:56.100
Ah!

119
00:06:56.100 --> 00:06:58.020
What?! Get off me!

120
00:06:58.020 --> 00:06:59.820
What's this afro?!

121
00:06:59.820 --> 00:07:00.900
Static electricity?!

122
00:07:01.350 --> 00:07:02.850
Exactly!

123
00:07:04.530 --> 00:07:07.240
Ahh! Dammit! Get off! Dammit!

124
00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.460
Ohhhhh... It's cold! It's cold!

125
00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:11.800
Clothes! Clothes!

126
00:07:13.770 --> 00:07:15.670
Clothes! Clothes! Clothes!

127
00:07:15.900 --> 00:07:17.370
Where are the clothes?!

128
00:07:17.370 --> 00:07:19.870
What's going on outside?
I hear a commotion...

129
00:07:19.870 --> 00:07:22.130
It's cold outside!
Where are my clothes?

130
00:07:22.510 --> 00:07:25.840
That's not what I asked.
What's happening outside?

131
00:07:25.840 --> 00:07:27.550
Oh, there's a fight.

132
00:07:27.550 --> 00:07:29.520
I see... You guys are okay, right?

133
00:07:29.520 --> 00:07:31.060
Yeah, so stay in bed.

134
00:07:31.060 --> 00:07:33.120
You can borrow my coat.

135
00:07:33.120 --> 00:07:35.660
What? But your clothes are ugly!

136
00:07:35.660 --> 00:07:37.390
They're more stylish than yours.

137
00:07:37.390 --> 00:07:38.230
Really?

138
00:07:38.230 --> 00:07:40.690
Well, it's alright
as long as they're warm.

139
00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:42.290
Alright!

140
00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:46.120
Oh... I wondered
what the fuss was about...

141
00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:50.070
That bastard!
Big mouth's got it coming!

142
00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:51.500
Dammit!

143
00:07:52.030 --> 00:07:54.750
What's with this afro?!
Get off! Get off!

144
00:07:58.240 --> 00:08:00.240
And I've got plenty more for ya!

145
00:08:01.150 --> 00:08:02.880
Marimo's Static Cling!

146
00:08:05.990 --> 00:08:08.340
What the hell?! Damn, they're gross!

147
00:08:09.400 --> 00:08:11.620
Hey, reindeer!
Don't just watch! Help me!

148
00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:12.560
Okay!

149
00:08:12.890 --> 00:08:15.560
Hurry, get 'em off!
Man, this is so gross!

150
00:08:15.560 --> 00:08:17.230
Can't believe it's just plain hair!

151
00:08:18.690 --> 00:08:20.500
Now they're stuck on me!
Take 'em back!

152
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:23.150
Ah! Don't give them back to me!
Keep one at least!

153
00:08:23.150 --> 00:08:24.300
No! They're gross!

154
00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:25.740
They're gross to me, too!

155
00:08:25.740 --> 00:08:27.170
– Stop it!
– Don't give them to me!

156
00:08:27.170 --> 00:08:29.490
What the heck are you guys doing?

157
00:08:28.540 --> 00:08:29.490
Ahh! Stop it!

158
00:08:29.490 --> 00:08:33.080
Hmph! They know nothing
about teamwork.

159
00:08:33.080 --> 00:08:35.220
I'll tell you one thing, though.

160
00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:37.460
Static Marimos look plain
but burn with style!

161
00:08:39.250 --> 00:08:41.580
Ack! Oh, crap!
He's gonna burn the afros!

162
00:08:41.580 --> 00:08:42.290
Here you go!

163
00:08:42.290 --> 00:08:44.560
Sure... Hey! Where are you going?!

164
00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:45.690
The decoy plan!

165
00:08:45.690 --> 00:08:48.260
D-Decoy plan? Am I the decoy?!

166
00:08:48.630 --> 00:08:49.880
Checkmate!

167
00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:53.350
Ah! Ow! Ow!
Snow! Snow! Snow!

168
00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:57.240
You...!

169
00:08:57.240 --> 00:08:58.390
Move!

170
00:08:58.930 --> 00:09:00.020
King Wapol!

171
00:09:00.020 --> 00:09:00.730
Oh, crap!

172
00:09:00.730 --> 00:09:01.350
Chopper!

173
00:09:03.880 --> 00:09:06.080
Yeah...! Now this is warm!

174
00:09:06.080 --> 00:09:06.880
Luffy!

175
00:09:06.880 --> 00:09:07.250
Huh?

176
00:09:07.250 --> 00:09:08.850
Grab my leg from there!

177
00:09:08.850 --> 00:09:10.070
Your leg? Sure!

178
00:09:10.990 --> 00:09:11.820
Like this?

179
00:09:11.820 --> 00:09:13.320
Right! Don't let go!

180
00:09:13.780 --> 00:09:15.260
Okay, got it!

181
00:09:15.260 --> 00:09:16.990
Armée de l'Air...

182
00:09:18.790 --> 00:09:21.290
Gum Shoot!

183
00:09:43.100 --> 00:09:43.980
Not bad...

184
00:09:46.540 --> 00:09:49.910
Th... Thank you.
You guys are amazing.

185
00:09:49.910 --> 00:09:53.380
Ah! Hey, Luffy! You jerk!
Isn't that Nami's jacket?!

186
00:09:53.380 --> 00:09:57.750
Yeah... Look! The hippo flew away
but big mouth's still alive!

187
00:09:57.750 --> 00:09:59.450
Take it off, you jerk!

188
00:09:59.830 --> 00:10:01.420
Your Majesty, are you alright?

189
00:10:01.420 --> 00:10:04.420
They're stronger than we thought.
We underestimated them!

190
00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:07.800
They just signed their death warrants!

191
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:09.380
Those bastards!

192
00:10:09.730 --> 00:10:10.860
– What?!
– What?!

193
00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:12.300
I'll show them...

194
00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:14.760
the true power
of the Munch-Munch Fruit!

195
00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:15.890
Your Majesty!

196
00:10:16.930 --> 00:10:19.970
I'll show them...
Munch-Munch Factory!

197
00:10:20.440 --> 00:10:21.540
Oh, he stood up!

198
00:10:21.540 --> 00:10:23.470
So I take it he's not normal?

199
00:10:23.470 --> 00:10:25.190
His body must be tough!

200
00:10:29.670 --> 00:10:31.340
Dalton is still alive.

201
00:10:33.470 --> 00:10:35.200
The Issie 20!

202
00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:38.650
His body is frozen. That's all.

203
00:10:38.650 --> 00:10:41.160
Will you leave him in our care?

204
00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:46.540
Hey, aren't those
the missing doctors?

205
00:10:46.540 --> 00:10:49.670
I heard that there
weren't any left in the country.

206
00:10:49.670 --> 00:10:54.900
That's the Issie 20, a group of doctors
who work exclusively for Wapol.

207
00:10:54.900 --> 00:10:56.430
That makes them bad doctors!

208
00:10:56.720 --> 00:10:58.800
That's right! We can't trust you!

209
00:10:58.800 --> 00:11:02.600
So we are supposed to leave Dalton in your care

210
00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:04.670
when you sold out
to Wapol... to that "king"?!

211
00:11:04.670 --> 00:11:06.650
What are you going
to do to Dalton?!

212
00:11:07.380 --> 00:11:10.150
If you want him to live,
then just do as we say!

213
00:11:12.950 --> 00:11:15.400
We are still doctors.

214
00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:18.570
Even though we were forced
to comply with Wapol and his men,

215
00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:22.090
we've always strived
to advance our medical knowledge

216
00:11:22.090 --> 00:11:24.540
to help the patients of this country!

217
00:11:27.900 --> 00:11:32.180
It was because a certain quack
taught us not to give up.

218
00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:39.930
We can't lose any more...
foolish men like him!

219
00:11:40.390 --> 00:11:44.400
Chess! Call out what I ate today!

220
00:11:44.400 --> 00:11:45.390
Yes, sir!

221
00:11:46.690 --> 00:11:51.200
Well... you ate one butter-sautéed cannon
and one raw cannon on the ship.

222
00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:55.900
Also cannonball and gunpowder salad
and a toasted house from the village.

223
00:11:56.200 --> 00:11:57.880
What kind of food is that?!

224
00:11:57.880 --> 00:11:59.620
Talk about omnivorous.

225
00:12:00.380 --> 00:12:01.870
Just watch...

226
00:12:01.870 --> 00:12:05.360
Anything I eat becomes 
my own flesh and blood...

227
00:12:08.460 --> 00:12:09.540
He's doing something!

228
00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:14.670
Huh?

229
00:12:14.670 --> 00:12:15.550
What's that?

230
00:12:15.880 --> 00:12:19.340
Munch-Munch Shock!

231
00:12:23.850 --> 00:12:26.600
Wapol House!

232
00:12:27.060 --> 00:12:27.640
A house?!

233
00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:29.190
So cool!

234
00:12:29.730 --> 00:12:33.150
Hold on to your surprise!
Now this is a kingly technique!

235
00:12:33.940 --> 00:12:36.610
Munch-Munch Factory!

236
00:12:39.490 --> 00:12:40.450
What the...?!

237
00:12:42.910 --> 00:12:45.200
H-He's eating his own men!

238
00:12:45.200 --> 00:12:46.910
He's eating them!

239
00:12:57.050 --> 00:13:00.930
Feast your eyes on this!
Come out, miraculous union!

240
00:13:01.220 --> 00:13:02.930
– Huh?!
– What?! Union?!

241
00:13:09.690 --> 00:13:13.560
I am the strongest warrior of Drum...

242
00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:22.740
Chessmarimo!

243
00:13:23.530 --> 00:13:26.660
Isn't that one... just riding
on the other's shoulders, though?

244
00:13:26.660 --> 00:13:28.500
Sweet!

245
00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:29.870
What's sweet about it?!

246
00:13:30.620 --> 00:13:32.460
Don't let your guard down.

247
00:13:32.460 --> 00:13:33.080
Huh?

248
00:13:33.750 --> 00:13:39.510
If they were that easy to beat,
the citizens would've never allowed them

249
00:13:39.510 --> 00:13:42.050
to stupidly exile the doctors.

250
00:13:42.630 --> 00:13:45.760
The Constitution
of the Kingdom of Drum, Article 1:

251
00:13:45.760 --> 00:13:49.060
"Those who don't comply
with the king's wishes shall die."

252
00:13:49.060 --> 00:13:51.190
It's this nation's founding principle!

253
00:13:51.190 --> 00:13:56.270
Which means this country is my country,
and that castle is my castle!

254
00:13:56.770 --> 00:14:00.780
Of all the flags out there,
don't you dare fly that quack's!

255
00:14:00.780 --> 00:14:02.950
It will ruin my castle!

256
00:14:18.550 --> 00:14:19.960
A Jolly Roger...

257
00:14:20.460 --> 00:14:22.630
Hey, reindeer. That flag...

258
00:14:25.590 --> 00:14:29.260
Nothing's impossible when a man
raises a skull and crossbones flag!

259
00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:32.520
That's what I told you, right, Chopper?!

260
00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:44.950
You bastard...
you attacked Doctor's flag!

261
00:14:48.280 --> 00:14:49.240
Doctor...

262
00:14:49.620 --> 00:14:51.700
even tried to save you!

263
00:14:52.660 --> 00:14:54.710
Chopper...

264
00:14:55.040 --> 00:14:57.130
Don't hold a grudge against humans.

265
00:14:59.710 --> 00:15:01.710
This country is sick right now.

266
00:15:02.130 --> 00:15:03.720
Why, Doctor...?

267
00:15:03.720 --> 00:15:06.260
A guy like him isn't worth saving!

268
00:15:10.260 --> 00:15:10.680
Wha...?

269
00:15:11.430 --> 00:15:12.930
I...

270
00:15:13.930 --> 00:15:18.060
I won't hit you...
if you leave this country!

271
00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:23.280
What are you saying, Chopper?!
You think he'll listen to you?!

272
00:15:24.110 --> 00:15:26.740
But... I thought...

273
00:15:27.030 --> 00:15:27.450
Hmph!

274
00:15:29.740 --> 00:15:30.580
Chopper!

275
00:15:36.330 --> 00:15:37.580
Hey, big mouth!

276
00:15:37.580 --> 00:15:38.170
Huh?!

277
00:15:41.040 --> 00:15:42.090
Straw Hat!

278
00:15:44.340 --> 00:15:47.430
You weren't even
a real pirate, were you?

279
00:15:47.430 --> 00:15:50.300
You don't know what
this pirate flag means

280
00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:52.510
because fake pirates risk nothing!

281
00:15:53.180 --> 00:15:54.640
Those words...

282
00:15:59.150 --> 00:16:03.190
Usopp and Mr. Bushido,
let's start heading up the mountain.

283
00:16:03.980 --> 00:16:04.690
Huh?

284
00:16:04.690 --> 00:16:06.150
I'm done waiting here!

285
00:16:06.150 --> 00:16:09.660
I'm worried that big avalanche
might have affected Luffy's group!

286
00:16:10.280 --> 00:16:12.870
Nami has a very high fever!

287
00:16:12.870 --> 00:16:14.040
If anything happened...

288
00:16:14.040 --> 00:16:15.580
You're worried about Nami...

289
00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:20.580
On top of that, you're worried about Dalton and Alabasta, huh?

290
00:16:22.840 --> 00:16:25.340
Vivi, calm down!

291
00:16:25.340 --> 00:16:27.510
You're shouldering too many burdens!

292
00:16:27.880 --> 00:16:28.590
What?

293
00:16:29.970 --> 00:16:34.350
Nami is with Luffy and Sanji.
I'm sure she's okay.

294
00:16:34.350 --> 00:16:37.480
They'll be fine! I believe in them!

295
00:16:38.690 --> 00:16:41.360
That's right... He's right...

296
00:16:43.520 --> 00:16:46.610
Usopp believes in his friends.

297
00:16:46.610 --> 00:16:49.400
That's why he's so calm about this.

298
00:16:50.660 --> 00:16:53.120
Thank you, Usopp. I...

299
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:56.200
You're just afraid of going
up the mountain, aren't you?

300
00:16:56.200 --> 00:17:01.170
B-But I heard that there are yetis
and bear-bunnies out there!

301
00:17:01.170 --> 00:17:03.090
Then say so from the start!

302
00:17:03.710 --> 00:17:06.760
It'll be fine. It's Luffy,
so he'll pull through!

303
00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:09.050
So I'm scared!
You got a problem with that?!

304
00:17:09.420 --> 00:17:10.260
Dalton!

305
00:17:10.260 --> 00:17:11.760
W-Wait!

306
00:17:14.260 --> 00:17:15.930
Ahh! Dalton!

307
00:17:15.930 --> 00:17:16.970
Dalton!

308
00:17:16.970 --> 00:17:19.100
Seriously, who's this Dalton guy?

309
00:17:20.600 --> 00:17:23.020
Dalton! You can't!

310
00:17:23.020 --> 00:17:27.570
Let me through! We can never again allow Wapol to set foot in the castle!

311
00:17:27.570 --> 00:17:30.110
You're not actually heading
to the castle, are you?!

312
00:17:30.110 --> 00:17:32.070
In your condition... Don't be crazy!

313
00:17:33.120 --> 00:17:36.030
If I don't fight now, then when will I?!

314
00:17:36.030 --> 00:17:41.000
If Wapol returns to the throne,
this country will be destroyed!

315
00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:45.960
In that condition,
there won't be a fight!

316
00:17:45.960 --> 00:17:48.960
We're no match for them, either...

317
00:17:49.380 --> 00:17:53.970
I will settle this,
even if I have to play dirty to win!

318
00:18:10.740 --> 00:18:13.030
Get on my back.
I'll take you to the castle.

319
00:18:14.820 --> 00:18:17.280
Come on, don't worry about it!

320
00:18:17.280 --> 00:18:19.540
Let's not waste your determination.

321
00:18:20.160 --> 00:18:22.000
Usopp...

322
00:18:23.330 --> 00:18:25.170
Hold on, okay?

323
00:18:25.170 --> 00:18:26.750
I will ensure...

324
00:18:27.460 --> 00:18:29.710
you reach the castle...

325
00:18:32.170 --> 00:18:33.680
Usopp...

326
00:18:37.930 --> 00:18:41.600
Hey, Usopp. I don't think
this is going to work...

327
00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:45.060
It'll work! I'll take you there!

328
00:18:45.060 --> 00:18:47.360
You're gonna fight
for this country, right?!

329
00:18:47.360 --> 00:18:49.610
You're gonna settle this, right?!

330
00:18:50.280 --> 00:18:54.570
Don't worry.
I'll definitely take you there!

331
00:18:57.070 --> 00:18:59.330
What's that moron thinking...

332
00:19:01.120 --> 00:19:04.040
We just have to go
up the mountain, right?

333
00:19:05.080 --> 00:19:06.330
Zoro...

334
00:19:08.670 --> 00:19:13.470
You jerk! You jerk! Usopp Punch!

335
00:19:09.840 --> 00:19:13.470
Ow! Ow! What're you doing?!

336
00:19:14.800 --> 00:19:17.970
And just when I was about
to show off my serious power!

337
00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:20.930
Yeah... I know.

338
00:19:20.930 --> 00:19:23.390
Serious power!

339
00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.390
Whoa, amazing, amazing...

340
00:19:24.270 --> 00:19:27.650
Wait! If you're set
on going to the castle,

341
00:19:29.730 --> 00:19:31.650
there's a ropeway you can use!

342
00:19:31.650 --> 00:19:35.820
There can't be. All the ropes
to the castle are gone now.

343
00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:38.030
There's one.

344
00:19:38.030 --> 00:19:40.530
Someone has reattached the white rope

345
00:19:40.530 --> 00:19:43.750
from a big tree at the edge
of Gyasta to the castle!

346
00:19:44.040 --> 00:19:45.460
Gyasta?

347
00:19:45.460 --> 00:19:48.750
That's the name of the town
where Dr. Kureha was last headed.

348
00:19:49.460 --> 00:19:52.300
What that flag means, Straw Hat?

349
00:19:53.960 --> 00:19:57.130
Stupid pirate flags have no meaning!

350
00:19:57.130 --> 00:19:59.430
That's why you're all hopeless!

351
00:19:59.430 --> 00:20:00.350
What'd you say?!

352
00:20:00.800 --> 00:20:05.310
A pirate flag isn't something
 you raise as a joke!

353
00:20:05.310 --> 00:20:06.690
What a hippo!

354
00:20:06.690 --> 00:20:10.150
The only way that I, the king,
would've raised one is because it's a joke!

355
00:20:10.150 --> 00:20:13.780
When I take down a hipposterous flag,
that doesn't mean you put it back up!

356
00:20:13.780 --> 00:20:16.190
You can't break it!

357
00:20:16.190 --> 00:20:19.990
The skull and crossbones
is a symbol of conviction!

358
00:20:22.490 --> 00:20:23.700
Dodge it! Watch out!

359
00:20:26.500 --> 00:20:27.330
Luffy!

360
00:20:27.830 --> 00:20:28.790
It's a direct hit!

361
00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:34.460
That's how you blow away a hippo!

362
00:20:54.780 --> 00:20:57.070
See? It's unbreakable.

363
00:20:57.860 --> 00:21:01.030
Huh? But how? He's an idiot!

364
00:21:01.570 --> 00:21:06.040
I don't know who the heck
this pirate flag belongs to...

365
00:21:06.040 --> 00:21:09.540
but this flag is someone's
pledge to risk their life.

366
00:21:09.540 --> 00:21:11.880
It's not raised as a joke!

367
00:21:14.920 --> 00:21:21.130
You don't just break a pirate flag
and laugh like an idiot about it!

368
00:21:26.720 --> 00:21:28.520
Incredible...

369
00:21:29.180 --> 00:21:31.060
So this is a pirate!

370
00:21:31.140 --> 00:21:32.560
What are pirates?

371
00:21:32.560 --> 00:21:35.570
Pirates are remarkable people
who roam the seas.

372
00:21:35.570 --> 00:21:40.530
Pirates are incredible! There are
countless people like that out at sea!

373
00:21:40.530 --> 00:21:43.530
Chopper, go out to sea some day.

374
00:21:47.240 --> 00:21:48.700
Hey, reindeer!

375
00:21:48.290 --> 00:21:48.700
Hm?

376
00:21:49.580 --> 00:21:53.210
I'm gonna beat these guys up now.
What do you wanna do?

377
00:21:53.960 --> 00:21:54.840
I...

378
00:21:54.840 --> 00:21:56.090
What are you saying?

379
00:21:56.090 --> 00:21:58.300
You damn hippo!

380
00:21:58.300 --> 00:22:02.970
If you're so determined to defend that flag,
then you'll die protecting it!

381
00:22:03.340 --> 00:22:05.680
You're not going anywhere!

382
00:22:06.050 --> 00:22:06.720
Hmm?!

383
00:22:09.850 --> 00:22:10.310
Ow!

384
00:22:10.310 --> 00:22:12.560
And there goes your backbone.

385
00:22:14.230 --> 00:22:17.190
It was bound to happen.
You're moving around too much!

386
00:22:17.650 --> 00:22:20.490
Doctor's Orders!

387
00:22:26.830 --> 00:22:29.080
What are you hippos doing?!

388
00:22:29.080 --> 00:22:33.250
Just stand there and watch!
I'll blow him to bits along with that flag!

389
00:22:33.790 --> 00:22:36.590
Your time's up, Straw Hat!

390
00:22:37.880 --> 00:22:40.550
Stop it!

391
00:22:41.460 --> 00:22:42.720
That's the idea!

392
00:22:42.720 --> 00:22:44.680
Get him, reindeer!

393
00:22:48.890 --> 00:22:51.140
King Wapol! Watch out!

394
00:22:56.270 --> 00:23:00.070
That brat's acting all brave
as if he's suddenly become a man.

395
00:23:03.570 --> 00:23:04.950
My apologies.

396
00:23:04.950 --> 00:23:07.990
I won't let you lay a finger on the king!

397
00:23:14.250 --> 00:23:17.540
There really are some
strange creatures in this world.

398
00:23:17.540 --> 00:23:20.840
Seems like you're that "yeti" that once

399
00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:22.920
got the citizens all riled up.

400
00:23:23.260 --> 00:23:26.930
You've been an outcast
your entire life.

401
00:23:26.930 --> 00:23:28.720
You poor monster.

402
00:23:28.720 --> 00:23:32.390
Why's an outcast
trying to save this country?

403
00:23:32.390 --> 00:23:33.680
Don't make me laugh!

404
00:23:33.680 --> 00:23:35.020
Shut up!

405
00:23:35.020 --> 00:23:38.270
Even if I don't have friends,
I can still fight!

406
00:23:39.360 --> 00:23:42.230
As long as Doctor's flag exists, I will...

407
00:23:42.230 --> 00:23:43.820
You do have friends!

408
00:23:46.910 --> 00:23:51.370
I'm your friend!

409
00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:05.220
Straw Hat!

410
00:24:10.140 --> 00:24:12.310
Whoa! Are you okay?!

411
00:24:12.310 --> 00:24:14.430
I'm just fine... since I'm rubber.

412
00:24:14.430 --> 00:24:15.140
Rubber?!

413
00:24:17.060 --> 00:24:20.230
Hey, reindeer.
Can you finish off that guy?

414
00:24:20.650 --> 00:24:22.730
That jerk? Piece of cake.

415
00:24:23.150 --> 00:24:24.690
Then it's decided.

416
00:24:25.440 --> 00:24:28.200
I'll take on big mouth!

417
00:24:29.700 --> 00:24:34.040
What impudence, Straw Hat,
flying around like that!

418
00:24:34.740 --> 00:24:36.790
I won't hesitate this time!

419
00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:39.000
You're gonna take me down?!

420
00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:40.630
Is that right, monster?

421
00:24:42.590 --> 00:24:44.210
What gives you the right...?

422
00:24:44.880 --> 00:24:48.220
Let me fight... you old ha–

423
00:24:48.220 --> 00:24:49.590
Just shut up and watch.

424
00:24:49.590 --> 00:24:53.180
If you keep flailing around,
you'll never walk on your own again.

425
00:24:53.680 --> 00:24:55.060
Don't worry.

426
00:24:55.060 --> 00:24:58.140
When push comes to shove,
my reindeer can handle things.

427
00:25:01.480 --> 00:25:05.150
My name is Tony Tony Chopper!

428
00:25:05.150 --> 00:25:07.990
It's a name that the world's
greatest doctor gave me!

429
00:25:08.650 --> 00:25:12.910
Doctor may have forgiven you
for mocking him,

430
00:25:12.910 --> 00:25:15.080
but I won't show you
the same mercy!

431
00:25:21.960 --> 00:25:23.790
I'm the one who'll show no mercy!

432
00:25:23.790 --> 00:25:25.590
I'll stomp you into the ground!

433
00:25:27.630 --> 00:25:29.380
Rumble Ball!
